<paragraph blockId="80.[264,1322,284,390]" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">
Comments: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall &amp; Cui" authorityYear="2005" box="[454,755,284,309]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Robustagramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mayense">
<emphasis box="[454,755,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Robustagramma mayense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall &amp; Cui" authorityYear="2005" box="[966,1315,284,309]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Robustagramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biangulatum">
<emphasis box="[966,1315,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="81">Robustagramma biangulatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, differing mostly in the shape of surstylus, the shape of basal portions of paired spermathecae, and development of postocellar bristles.
